</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[93,1050,809,1662]" pageId="31" pageNumber="1546">near posterior to ventral margins (gure 13A). Surstylus not expanded at posteroventral corner, with about ve short prensisetae on distal margin, a few thin setulae on outer ap, and several on ventrapical part of inner surface (gure 13B). Tenth sternite nearly bilobed, but not separated mid-dorsally, laterally narrowly fused to surstyli; lateral lobe-like process somewhat oblong (gure 13B). Anterior portion of hypandrium entirely thin (gure 13C). Parameres separated from each other, lobeshaped, slightly incised at posterolateral corner, each with apical, sclerotized process and six to seven sensilla on distal mesal surface (gure 13D). Aedeagus separated into a pair of somewhat sinuated rods, each fused to base of paramere (gure 13D). Vertical lobe of gonopod spade-shaped, strongly protruded and sclerotized apically gure 13C). Ejaculatory apodeme: apical plate with four pits per side; stalk thick, long (gure 13F).</paragraph>
